Database migrations (Alembic)
=============================

`alembic/env.py` pulls the schema from `app.db.models` (Base.metadata) and the
connection URL from `app.config.DATABASE_URL`, so migrations track the models
and target the same DB as the app (SQLite in dev, Postgres in prod).

Common commands (run from the repo root):

    alembic current                      # what revision the DB is at
    alembic history                      # list migrations
    alembic upgrade head                 # apply all pending migrations
    alembic downgrade -1                 # roll back one
    alembic revision --autogenerate -m "add X"   # create a migration from model changes

After changing a model, ALWAYS create a migration (don't rely on create_all):

    alembic revision --autogenerate -m "describe change"
    # review the generated file in alembic/versions/, then:
    alembic upgrade head

Dev vs prod
-----------
- SQLite (dev): `app.db.init_db` still runs create_all for zero-setup, and the
  dev DB has been `alembic stamp`-ed at the baseline. Prefer `alembic upgrade
  head` for schema changes so dev matches prod.
- Postgres (prod): init_db skips create_all; the schema is Alembic-owned. On
  deploy: set DATABASE_URL=postgresql+psycopg://… and run `alembic upgrade head`
  (install psycopg — see requirements-api.txt).

SQLite note: env.py enables batch mode (render_as_batch) so ALTER-style
migrations work on SQLite too.
